olonize another's experience with one's own. Haunting Encounters is a sensitive and perceptive application of theory to real-world concerns. It draws together the fields of postcolonial fiction and narrative ethics and suggests original modes of engagement between readers and books that promise new ways of looking at the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aAmerican fictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aAmerican fictiony21st centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aCommonwealth fiction (English)y20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aDifference (Philosophy) in literature. 0aGhost storiesxHistory and criticism. 0aGhosts in literature. 0aMemory in literature. 0aPsychic trauma in literature. 0aSupernatural in literature. 0aTransnationalism in literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Semiotics & Theory.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCOR eBook-Package Pilot Project 2017z978311066587108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell Univ. Press eBook-Package Pilot Project 2016-2017z978311060673740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/9781501713828zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501713828.jpg  a978-3-11-060673-7  Cornell Univ. Press eBook-Package Pilot Project 2016-2017c2016d2017  a978-3-11-066587-1  COR eBook-Package Pilot Project 2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG